<HL>
   Crystal Brands' Net Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
04/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CBR
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   SOUTHPORT, Conn. -- Crystal Brands Inc. said first-quarter
net income rose 9% to $6.6 million, or 73 cents a share,
aided by higher profit margins and lower expenses and
interest costs.
   The apparel maker's year-earlier profit was $6.1 million,
or 67 cents a share. First-quarter sales fell 2% to $218.8
million from $223.3 million.
